The federal government has handed over a livestock health centre it built and equipped in Kuje Area Council to the Federal Capital Territory Administration (FCTA). During the inauguration of the centre on Wednesday, the Director and Chief Veterinary Officer of Nigeria, Dr Maimuna Habib, disclosed that the project was executed to provide quality animal healthcare services to livestock farmers and pastoralists. She said the centre was constructed by the veterinary and pest control services department of the Federal Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development to help rural dwellers improve on their livestock production. 